A GROWING INTEREST IN SOLAR ENERGY.
FRESNO, Calif..
The first Saturday in October was clear, dry and drenched in bright sunlight -- ideal for the solar panels converting light to electricity at Harry Kubetz and Gary Burton's home in Northport, N.Y. "Today is a peak power day," Burton said, looking up at a rooftop covered with 80 solar panels.
"We're probably producing enough power to meet our demand for the day."
